<span id="freeTextContainer17072304639926264229">This was the pseudonymous Parker&apos;s first novel in his style; perhaps because I fell in love with his later work, I wasn&apos;t able to devour this one with as much relish. All his definitive themes are here, though, just under the surface, almost exploratory: morality, necessity, love, ambiguity. <br/><br/>Untempered KJ Parker, but the material is as fine as ever. </span>
